## Introduction
This report analyzes a dataset containing information about prompt and completion tokens alongside their corresponding model latency. The main objectives are to explore the token distributions, investigate potential correlations between token counts and latency, and create a regression model to understand these relationships better.

## Data Overview
The dataset consists of 600 records with the following columns:
- `prompt_token_count`: Number of tokens in the prompt.
- `completion_token_count`: Number of tokens in the completion.
- `model_latency`: Latency of the model in processing the request.
- `model`: Type of model (in this case, all entries are from 'claude-3-5-sonnet').

## Conclusion and Actionable Insights
